@dubee new actions would be stored with `code` as object. That format was already being used by Java actions so should work fine. 

```json
{
"code": {
      "attachmentName": "couch:f41be90d-5656-47f5-9be9-0d5656f7f555",
      "attachmentType": "application/java-archive",
      "length": 32768,
      "digest": "sha256-5a373715b8cdcd608059debe9dae2ad95087eb5322321d1d0b862f8330a0e54d"
    }
}
```

Is that you were looking for or you meant something else?

@rabbah Sorry for not been responsive. I was out for vacation.
Could you please have another look on this PR. 
With the latest commit only the actor system is left as additional implicit parameter.

`ConnectionError`s are resolved now, using keepalive = false (vs `Connection:close` header). 

@markusthoemmes please have a look when possible.

@rabbah @csantanapr this does NOT currently implement any change to runtimes manifest, but since none of this is enabled by default, it is low (or none) impact.
